data.name: Herb-Crusted Beef Tenderloin with Garlic Mashed Potatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: A succulent beef tenderloin coated with fragrant herbs, paired with creamy garlic mashed potatoes for a comforting meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, mix the chopped rosemary, thyme, olive oil, salt, and black pepper to create a paste.
Rub this herb mixture all over the beef tenderloin.
Place the tenderloin on a baking sheet and roast in the oven for about 25-30 minutes, or until it reaches your desired doneness (135°F for medium-rare).
While the beef is cooking, boil the potatoes in salted water until fork-tender, about 15-20 minutes.
Drain the potatoes and return them to the pot. Add the minced garlic, butter, and milk, then mash until smooth and creamy. Season with salt to taste.
Once the beef is done, let it rest for about 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve the slices of beef with a generous helping of garlic mashed potatoes.
